Marquez (0.1.0)

License: Apache 2.0

Marquez is an open source metadata service for the collection, aggregation, and visualization of a data ecosystem's metadata.

Namespaces

Create a namespace

Creates a new namespace object. A namespace enables the contextual grouping of related jobs and datasets. Namespaces must contain only letters (a-z, A-Z), numbers (0-9), or underscores (_). A namespace is case-insensitive with a maximum length of 1024 characters. Note jobs and datasets will be unique within a namespace, but not across namespaces.

path Parameters
namespace
required
string <= 1024 characters
Example: "wework"

The name of the namespace.

Request Body schema: application/json
owner
required
string

The owner of the namespace.

description
string

The description of the namespace.

Responses

200

OK

put /namespaces/{namespace}

Local API server

http://localhost:5000/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}

Request samples

  • Payload
application/json
Copy
 Expand all Collapse all
{
  • "owner": "dataengineering",
  • "description": "A namespace for core jobs and datasets at wework."
}

Response samples

  • 200
application/json
Copy
 Expand all Collapse all
{
  • "name": "wework",
  • "createdAt": "2019-05-09T19:49:24.201Z",
  • "owner": "dataengineering",
  • "description": "A namespace for core jobs and datasets at wework."
}

Jobs

Create a job

Creates a new job object. All job objects are immutable and are uniquely identified by a generated ID. Marquez will create a version of a job each time the contents of the object is modified. For example, the location of a job may change over time resulting in new versions. The accumulated versions can be listed, used to rerun a specific job version or possibly help debug a failed job run.

path Parameters
namespace
required
string <= 1024 characters
Example: "wework"

The name of the namespace.

job
required
string <= 1024 characters
Example: "room_bookings_7_days"

The name of the job.

Request Body schema: application/json
inputDatasetUrns
required
Array of string <URN>

The URN list of input datasets.

outputDatasetUrns
required
Array of string <URN>

The URN list of output datasets.

location
required
string <URI>

The URI of the job source or artifact.

description
string

The description of the job.

Responses

200

OK

put /namespaces/{namespace}/jobs/{job}

Local API server

http://localhost:5000/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/jobs/{job}

Request samples

  • Payload
application/json
Copy
 Expand all Collapse all
{
  • "inputDatasetUrns":
    [
    • "urn:wework:wedata.room_bookings",
    • "urn:meetup:analytics.scheduled_events"
    ],
  • "outputDatasetUrns":
    [
    • "urn:wework:wedata.room_bookings_7_days"
    ],
  • "location": "https://github.com/wework/jobs/commit/124f6089ad4c5fcbb1d7b33cbb5d3a9521c5d32c",
  • "description": "Determine weekly room booking occupancy patterns."
}

Create a job run

Creates a new job run object.

path Parameters
namespace
required
string <= 1024 characters
Example: "wework"

The name of the namespace.

job
required
string <= 1024 characters
Example: "room_bookings_7_days"

The name of the job.

Request Body schema: application/json
nominalStartTime
string <date-time>

The nominal start time of the job.

nominalEndTime
string <date-time>

The nominal end time of the job.

runArgs
string

The runtime arguments of the job. JSON encoded.

Responses

201

CREATED

post /namespaces/{namespace}/jobs/{job}/runs

Local API server

http://localhost:5000/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/jobs/{job}/runs

 Expand all Collapse all

}

Response samples

application/json
Copy

Create a datasource

Creates a new datasource object. A datasource is the physical location of a dataset such as a table in PostgreSQL, or topic in Kafka. A datasource enables the grouping of physical datasets to their physical source.

Request Body schema: application/json
name
required
string

The name of the datasource.

connectionUrl
required
string <URL>

The url to be used to connect to the datasource.

Responses

200

OK

post /datasources

Local API server

http://localhost:5000/api/v1/datasources
